<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Makes Progress, Meets Aide in Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
is making satisfactory progress in recovering from gastric ulcer
and met Saturday with a senior aide in the hospital, his spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
"The fact that today he has had a long meeting with
presidential administration chief Nikolai Bordyuzha now speaks
best of the president's condition," said presidential press
secretary Dmitry Yakushkin.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin, 67, was rushed to Moscow's Central Clinical Hospital
on January 17 with an acute gastric ulcer bleeding.
</P>
<P>
He met with Bordyuzha and the two discussed the country's
political and economic developments, Yakushkin said.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin signed several orders, one of which appoints Foreign
Minister Igor Ivanov as presidential representative to the
parliamentary debate of ratification of the friendship and
cooperation treaty between Russia and Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed international matters such as Moscow's
diplomatic efforts over Iraq and the Yugoslav province of Kosovo,
Itar-Tass reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
