<HEADLINE> Palestinians Granted Telephone Country Code </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The International
Telecommunications Union (ITU) has granted the Palestinian
self-rule areas their own country code this month, local media
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The new country code, 970, which will be operational from
March, will replace the current one designated for Israel, 972.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian National Authority (PNA) said in a statement
following a weekly cabinet meeting late Friday that the ITU
decision was "a recognition of Palestinian national independence
and sovereignty."
</P>
<P>
The PNA has independent telecommunications, with over 150,000
lines in the West Bank and Gaza Strip, but it has up to now had to
use the country code for Israel.
</P>
<P>
Israel had strongly opposed the proposal by some Arab
countries to grant a country code for the Palestinians, saying
the status of the Palestinian-controlled areas has to be
determined in peace negotiations.
</P>
<P>
But the ITU, an affiliate of the United Nations, decided in a
November meeting to reserve the 970 code for the PNA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
