<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-23 18:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Palestinians Demand Boycott of Products from </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) has called on the international community to
boycott products made in Jewish settlements on the
Israeli-occupied Palestinian territories.
</P>
<P>
The boycott call, a response to Israel's suspension of the Wye
peace agreement, came in a statement published after the weekly
meeting of the Palestinian cabinet on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
"In light of Israel's freeze of the agreements, the
Palestinian leadership asks all economic blocs to boycott products
made in Jewish settlements," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The statement noted that such a move "would assert
international objection to settlement building on Palestinian
lands," and would show the efforts of the international community
to push the peace process forward.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet specifically asked the United States, Japan, Russia
and the European Union to took part in the boycott.
</P>
<P>
Israel and the PNA signed the interim peace accord last
October, under which Israel will withdraw from another 13 percent
of the West Bank in return for tougher measures taken by the PNA
to fight terrorism.
</P>
<P>
However, Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu announced
last December to suspend the implementation of the agreement in
the excuse that the PNA had not fulfilled its commitments.
</P>
<P>
Denying the charges, the PNA pointed out that the suspension
was simply part of Netanyahu's attempt to rally support from
right-wing voters before the coming early general elections of
Israel in May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
