<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania to Proclaim Year 2000 "The Eminescu Year" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The Culture Ministry of
Romania is to proclaim the year 2000 "The Eminescu Year", to mark
150 years since the birth of the country's greatest poet Mihai
Eminescu.
</P>
<P>
"The Eminescu Year" would be enshrined in the UNESCO calendar,
the national Rompres news agency Saturday quoted Minister of
Culture Ion Caramitru as saying.
</P>
<P>
Eminescu transformed Romanian poetry both in form and in
content. Simplicity of language, masterly handling of rhyme and
verse form, profitability of thought and plasticity of expression
made him the creator of a school of poetry that dominated Romanian
thought and expression of Romanian writers and poets at the end of
the 19th and the beginning of the 20th century.
</P>
<P>
His poems have been translated into many languages in the
world. "The evening star" is one of Eminescu's best-known poems.
</P>
<P>
Mihai Eminescu, also a newspaperman, writer, philosopher and
translator, was born on January 15, 1850, and died at the age of
39.  
</P>
</TEXT>
