<HEADLINE> Israeli Defense Minister Dismissed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January (Xinhua)-- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu fired Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai, who is accused
of not supporting the policy of the government.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu said in a statement that Mordechai has been driven by
his personal ambition and not fully supported the policies of the
government.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to Mordechai, Netanyahu said "you will no longer be
able to serve as Defense Minister in the government headed by
Likud. Your tenure will officially come to an end 48 hours after
this letter is delivered to you."
</P>
<P>
"I intend to appoint a replacement for you immediately,
someone loyal to Likud principles and ideology, who is ready to
serve the state of Israel loyally, without giving preference to
his personal interests," Netanyahu said in his letter.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu, who is campaigning for the early general elections
scheduled for May, is reportedly to have asked Moshe Arense, his
old friend, to replace Mordechai and he got a positive answer.
</P>
