<HEADLINE> Syria Vows to Help Make the Arab FM Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Syria vowed to help make
successful Sunday's Arab Foreign Ministers meeting at the
Cairo-based Arab League headquarters, the Syrian Arab News Agency
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The statement was made by Syrian Foreign Minister Farouq
al-Sharaa, who arrived in Cairo Saturday to attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian minister hopes that the meeting will be conducive to
the revitalization of Arab solidarity and the achievement of a
common Arab stance.
</P>
<P>
Sharaa called on the meeting to help avert the military actions
against Iraq and lift the United Nations sanctions on Iraq
following its 1990 invasion of Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, initially scheduled for late last December after a
series of air strikes by the United States and Britain on Iraq in
mid December, was put off to January 24 in the wake of some Arab
countries' call for better preparations.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will focus on the Iraqi issue and a Yemeni call for
an Arab summit on Iraq. 
</P>
</TEXT>
