<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Warplane Attacks Iraqi Missile Sites U.S. Warplane Attacks Iraqi Missile Sites </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 24 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. warplane patrolling
the northern no-fly zone in Iraq on Sunday attacked an Iraqi
surface-to-air missile site, the Pentagon said.
</P>
<P>
A U.S. F-15E fired a precision-guided missile on the Iraqi
installation after aircraft in the area reported they were
illuminated by an Iraqi surface-to-air missile system, said Air
Force Lt. Col. Dennis Linn at the Pentagon.
</P>
<P>
A pilot whose plane is illuminated, or "painted" by radar, assu
mes he is about to be fired upon.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred at 10:45 a.m. Iraqi time.
</P>
<P>
Linn did not immediately know if the planes returned safely to
the NATO base in incirlik, Turkey.
</P>
<P>
There were no incidents in the southern no-fly zone on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, American warplanes dropped laser-guided bombs on
two surface-to-air missile sites in southern Iraq. 
</P>
</TEXT>
