<HEADLINE> Chinese PLA Chief of General Staff Visits Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese People's
Liberation Army (PLA) Chief of the General Staff General Fu
Quanyou arrived here Sunday night for a five-day official and
goodwill visit to Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Fu said in a written statement upon his arrival at the Kuala
Lumpur International Airport that China and Malaysia are friendly
close neighbors and there exists a profound friendship between the
peoples of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said since the establishment of diplomatic relations between
China and Malaysia, the bilateral relations have maintained a
sound momentum of development, and the exchanges and cooperation
in each field have been well under way.
</P>
<P>
China attaches great importance to developing friendly and
cooperative relations with Malaysia, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said his visit, the first official and goodwill visit ever
paid to Malaysia by the Chinese PLA Chief of the General Staff,
aimed to "further promote understanding, strengthen trust,
develop friendship and enhance cooperation."
</P>
<P>
During the visit at the invitation of Malaysian Defense Forces
Chief General Mohd Zahidi Bin Hj Zainuddin, Fu is scheduled to
call on Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad, Defense
Minister Abang Abu Bakar and his host Zahidi.
</P>
<P>
He is also scheduled to visit military establishments and
academic institutions.
</P>
<P>
General Fu, accompanied by, among others, Lieutenant General
Guo Boxiong, Chief of the PLA Lan Zhou Military Area Command;
Major General Huang Jiang, Chief of Staff of the PLA South China
Sea Fleet; Major General Li Jinshan, Chief of Staff of the PLA
Shen Yang Military Area Air Force Command and Major General Li
Donghui, Deputy Director General of the Foreign Affairs office
(Ministry of Defense), arrived here after an official and goodwill
visit to Australia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
