<HEADLINE> Italian Skater Sets 1,000m World Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Fabio Carta of Italy set a new
world record of one minute, 27.454 seconds in the 1,000-meter
short-track speedskating at the European Championship in
Oberstdorf of Germany on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Carta, Olympic silver medalist, beat the old mark of 1:28.230
set by Marc Gagnon of Canada in Seoul, South Korea, on April 4,
1997.
</P>
<P>
Late Saturday, another Italian, Marinella Canclini, set a
world record over 500 meters, clocking 44.620 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Canclini beat the previous record of Yevgenia Radanova of
Bulgaria of 44.690, set last November 8 in Szekesfehervar,
Hungary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
