<HEADLINE> Publicity Minister Stresses Conforming to CPC Central Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Ding Guangen,a member of the
Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee and Minister of Publicity, said yesterday that
publicity departments nationwide should keep in line with the CPC
Central Committee in the new year.
</P>
<P>
Ding made the remark at a four-day national conference on
publicity work which ended yesterday, adding that more positive
publicity should be disseminated to commemorate the 20th
anniversary of China's reform and opening-up, the 80th
anniversary of the May 4th Movement, and to welcome the handover
of Macao to the motherland, as well as the approaching new
century.
</P>
<P>
Ding said that publicity workers should bear in mind people's
interests, pay great attention to people's ideas, and reflect
people's wishes, while working whole-heartedly for the happiness
of the people.
</P>
<P>
"More efforts should be made to publicize current topics, and
positive reporting should still be the mainstream," he said.
</P>
<P>
The minister encouraged publicity workers to respect
knowledge and talent, adding that more communication between
publicity workers and talented people from all walks of life will
be beneficial to China. 
</P>
