<DOCNO> XIE19990124.0051 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Economy Grows Rapidly in Anhui </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Private enterprises are playing
an increasingly important role in economic development and the
reemployment of the jobless in east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
The combined output value for these enterprises reached 19.4
billion yuan in 1998, accounting for 6.8 percent of the
province's gross domestic product.
</P>
<P>
A total of 123,000 laid-off workers were reemployed in private
enterprises in the province last year.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has issued a series of preferential
policies to support private enterprises, including a loosening of
limitations on management activities and amounts of registered
capital.
</P>
<P>
The Anhui Provincial Administration for Industry and Commerce
has handled a number of cases involving the infringement of
private-business profits. The city of Huangshan's Administration
for Industry and Commerce ruled that it should not take more than
three working days to accept registration for issuing
private-enterprise licenses.
</P>
<P>
The province has also set aside more than 100 million yuan to
support high-tech private businesses. At present, there are more
than 100 high-tech private enterprises in the State-level Hefei
High-Tech and New Technological Industrial Development Zone.
</P>
</TEXT>
