<HEADLINE> Taliban Rule Out Talks with U.S. on Osama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban militia
Sunday ruled out any possibility of talks with the United States
on Saudi dissident Osama bin Laden.
</P>
<P>
"There is no possibility of dialogue with the United States on
Osama and reports in this connection are totally baseless," the
Taliban's representative in Islamabad Saeedur Rahman Haqqani said
here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Taliban's relations with the United States
have been strained since the U.S. cruise missiles struck
Afghanistan in August last year.
</P>
<P>
He dismissed reports of any kind of contact between the United
States and the Taliban.
</P>
<P>
"Osama is a guest of the Afghan nation," he said, adding that
the militia "would fully protect him as a trust of the nation and
would never commit any betrayal in this regard." 
