<HEADLINE> China's Border Defense Seize 900 Million Yuan in Smuggled Goods in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- China's border defense force
cracked some 850 smuggling cases in 1998 involving a total of 900
million yuan worth of smuggled goods, the Ministry of Public
Security said today.
</P>
<P>
Among the confiscated goods were 550 ships, 329 automobiles,
260 motorbikes, 170,000 tons of oil products, 62,809 cases of
cigarettes, over 63 million in counterfeit yuan, the Chinese
currency, and large quantities of food, wine, and electric
appliances.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry said that smuggling has become rampant in regions
such as south China's Guangdong Province, the Pearl River Delta,
and the Yangtze River Delta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
