<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Increases Tax-Refund Rates for Some Export Commodities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- China has increased tax
refunding rates for some exported commodities beginning on
January 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Ministry of Finance disclosed that the
export-tax refund rate has been raised to 17 percent for
electro-mechanical products including electronics products,
meters, transportation instruments, and some machinery and
equipment.
</P>
<P>
The export-tax refund rate also has been raised to 13 percent
for agricultural machinery, textile fibers, porcelain, rolled
steel and cement.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural products now will have a five percent export-tax
refund rate, and the rate for raw chemicals, plastic products,
toys and products related to tourism is now 11 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
