<HEADLINE> CPPCC Vice-Chairwoman Meets ROK Former Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Qian Zhengying,
vice-chairwoman of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) National Committee, met here today with Lee
Soo Sung, former prime minister of the Republic of Korea (ROK).
</P>
<P>
Qian said that Sino-ROK relations have witnessed smooth
development in various fields since the two countries forged
diplomatic ties, adding that Lee's visit to China at the
beginning of 1999 would help advance bilateral links.
</P>
<P>
Lee expressed his hope that ROK-China relations would continue
to grow in the years to come.
</P>
<P>
Lee is here on a visit at the invitation of the CPPCC National
Committee. 
</P>
