<HEADLINE> Over 60 Killed in Fighting in Afghanistan: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 24 (Xinhua) -- More than 60 people were
killed in the past few days in fighting between the Taliban
militia and opposition forces in northern and northwestern
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan on
Sunday, 38 Taliban troops were killed in the last two days in the
fighting with forces loyal to ethnic Tajik commander Ahmad Shah
Masood in northwest Faryab province.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Abdullah, spokesman for the anti-Taliban
alliance, as saying that 12 opposition troops were killed and 28
others wounded in the fighting around the Faryab town of Sheerin
Tagab.
</P>
<P>
He said that fighting escalated in Afghanistan after an ethnic
Uzbek commander Makhtome, who had been working with the Taliban
for several years, switched sides with Masood the day before
Friday.
</P>
<P>
About 350 Taliban fighters were captured in Faryab province,
the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said that about 12 Taliban troops were killed and
60 others captured during a recent uprising in the northern
province of Balkh. 
