<HEADLINE> Iran Opposes U.S. Military Base in Azerbaijan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Iran has voiced its deep concern
over a U.S. military base which is reportedly to be set up in
Azerbaijan Republic.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a flag hoisting ceremony on Saturday, Hassan
Firouzabadi, the chief of the joint staff of Iran's armed forces,
said negotiations are currently underway for the setting up of the
base.
</P>
<P>
"The Israelis and the Americans are approaching us from the
north and we are carefully watching their movements and their
propaganda," the official said.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian armed forces is composed of the army, the Islamic
Revolutionary Guards Corp and security forces under the command of
the supreme leader and Commander-in-Chief Ayatollah Ali Khamenei.
</P>
<P>
The joint staff of the armed forces is responsible for
coordinating the three military forces in the country.
</P>
<P>
Firouzabadi also warned the U.S. that the people in Aran,
Azerbaijan, where the U.S. is alleged to set up the base, are
Shiite Muslims with Iranian blood in their veins.
</P>
<P>
"The Americans and the Israelis must pay attention to this
important point," he added.
</P>
<P>
Azerbaijan's State Adviser on Foreign Policy Vafa Gulizade on
Saturday underlined the need for the presence of U.S., Turkish
or NATO forces in his country.
</P>
<P>
Azerbaijan's security is at stake because there are forces
in Russia to revive the former Soviet Union, Gulizade said.
</P>
<P>
He also said Russia is equipping Armenia with modern
weaponry and Turkey should not remain silent in this connection.
</P>
<P>
However, Azerbaijan's ambassador to Tehran Abbasali Hasanov
recently strongly rejected a report on the establishment of a
U.S. base in Azerbaijan and termed it as "baseless." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
