<HEADLINE> Insurance Giant Eyes Greater Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The China Pacific Insurance
Co. Ltd, one of the top insurers in China, has vowed to increase
its market share this year based on surging business in 1998.
</P>
<P>
To meet the target, the company is expected to focus on expandi
ng business in cities and developed areas. It will also adopt
new accounting rules in line with international norms this year,
and speed up the computerization of its business management
system.
</P>
<P>
The value insured by the company surged by 26.8 percent in
1998 to 3.8 trillion yuan (457.8 billion U.S. dollars), with the
profits rocketing 60 percent to 380 million yuan, according to a
company report.
</P>
<P>
The rapid business growth could be attributed to increased
market promotion, improved financial management and the unified
handling of premiums income, said the company president Wang
Guoliang at an annual conference.
</P>
<P>
The company also set up a joint-venture insurance company with
a leading US insurance company last year, aiming to introduce
advanced insurance techniques and management expertise.  
</P>
