<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, January 24 (Xinhua) -- A member of the Israeli allied
South Lebanon Army (SLA) was seriously wounded in south Lebanon
Saturday night in an attack by the Lebanese guerrilla group
Hezbollah.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah, or Party of God, launched the attack on a SLA's post
at Kalkab village in the eastern sector of the Israeli occupied
border zone in south Lebanon, the Orient radio reported Sunday.
</P>
