<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Five Serb civilians abducted by Kosovo rebels were
released on Saturday after the mediation by the cease-fire
verification mission of the Organization for Security and
Cooperation in Europe (OSCE).
</P>
<P>
The five Serbs, including two women, were turned over to
members of the OSCE cease-fire verification mission. Meanwhile
Yugoslav authorities on Saturday also freed nine Kosovo
Liberation Army (KLA) members who had been in custody for more
than a month. (Kosovo-Hostages)
</P>
