Saturday traveled to the southern neutral area with a
counter-proposal for prisoner exchange in an effort to get the
peace talks with the FARC rebels back on track.
</P>
<P>
Colombian President Andres Pastrana launched the peace talks
with the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) on January
7 in a bid to end the country's civil conflict, which has been
going on for nearly 50 years. However, the FARC on Tuesday said
it was freezing the talks until the government cracks down on
right-wing paramilitary groups. The FARC also offered to exchange
350 captured police and soldiers for 452 jailed rebels.
