<HEADLINE> 20,000 Foreigners Receive Training in Business Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 24 (Xinhua) -- About 20,000 foreigners have
attended various kinds of training courses in business Chinese in
China over the past two decades, according to information from a
recent symposium on teaching of business Chinese for foreign
students held in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Teaching of business Chinese for foreign students, which
originated when China started to open to the outside world in
1978, has become an important part of the country's teaching of
Chinese specially designed for foreign students and is most
successfully done in Beijing and Shanghai, said sources at the
symposium.
</P>
<P>
China now has more than 324,700 overseas-financed businesses
and, many representatives of these companies learn business
Chinese before they perform their duties as representatives of
foreign businesses in China.  
