<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Funaki Wins Large Hill Event in World Cup Jumping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Olympic gold medalist Kazuyoshi
Funaki took the large hill event, the second of the weekend's two
ski jumping World Cup events, at Sapporo, Japan on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese scored 274.4 points to beat overnight winner Mart
in Schmitt of Germany to the second place. Schmitt had 272.1
points while Japan's Hideharu Miyahira, runner-up on Saturday,
was third at 267.7.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's victory was Funaki's second this season following his
triumph in Engelberg, Switzerland, on January 10.
</P>
<P>
After 17 of a scheduled 30 events this season, Janne Ahonen of
Finland still remains atop the World Cup standings with 1,291
points, followed by Schmitt's 1,058 points and Funaki's 1,023
points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
