<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Selects Cricketers for 1999 World Cup Cricket </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh has initially
selected 30 cricketers to form a national team for the 1999 World
Cup Cricket to be held in England later this year.
</P>
<P>
The cricketers have been requested to report at the Bangladesh
Cricket Board office on February 1, to take part in the coaching
camp at Savar, on the outskirts of the capital city, with their
cricket instruments, The New Nation newspaper reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 30-strong squad will be reduced to 19 in the third week of
February, and a 15-member contingent will finally be announced in
the third week of March to represent the country to compete in
the World Cup Cricket from May 20 to June 12.
</P>
<P>
Cricket is the most popular sport in Bangladesh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
