<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The Phnom Penh municipality
is to launch a fresh crackdown next month on gambling and gaming
outlets in the city and to clearly define the anti-gambling and
gaming laws.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to clearly define the categories of gambling,
so that necessary action can be taken against the operators of
these outlets and police can clearly carry out the orders issued
to them, the Vision newspaper reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It was said that a previous order to all the seven police
districts to shut down video games and other gambling outlets
within 200 meters from any school was ineffective. Some complained
they could not define what were the forms of gambling.
</P>
<P>
"We are determined to shut down all gambling and gaming
facilities in February and we will start with those outlets
located close to the schools as they were distracting students
from attending classes and also encouraged petty thefts by
students and youngsters," Mann Chheun, chief of the Municipality's
cabinet, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
"Any outlet which does not adhere to the authority's
instructions will have their equipment confiscated and the premise
sealed," he added.
</P>
<P>
There has been an alarming increase in the number of students
playing truant from schools. They are normally found in the video
games arcades or snooker centers located near the schools.
</P>
<P>
Police officials said students were also resorting to extorting
money from their class or school mates to feed their passion for
the games which is addictive. 
</P>
