<HEADLINE> China to Increase Timber Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- China is expected to increase
timber imports this year in the wake of the nationwide logging
ban in order to fill in the strong demand in domestic market, the
Business Weekly reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
(MOFTEC) decided at the end of last year to cancel controls on
timber importers, so that companies with foreign trade rights can
engage in timber import business.
</P>
<P>
"We can completely depend on imports to solve the problem of
inadequate timber supply following the output reduction," Chinese
Premier Zhu Rongji said when he was inspecting the flooded areas
in northeast China last year.
</P>
<P>
The devastating floods that swept across China last Summer
have created demands for timber products in reconstruction, and
resulted in a ban on the logging of natural forests.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the country will reduce timber production
by 10 million cubic meters a year.
</P>
<P>
The massive infrastructure projects launched by the central
government also fueled the demand for timber products.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, imports will be very important to plug the growing
demand-supply gap of timber products this year, experts said.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
</TEXT>
