<HEADLINE> Road Accident Kills Five in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Five members of a family died
Saturday in a traffic accident occurred on the Montes Claros road
in the Northern Brazilian state of Minas Gerais.
</P>
<P>
A car with five persons aboard jumped into the incoming lane
and collided with a Mercedes Benz truck, the Federal Highway
Police officers said.
</P>
<P>
Road accidents occur frequently in the Montes Claros road,
which are very near the beaches, the policemen said.
</P>
<P>
Celso Ribeiro da Silva, 60, the driver, and his four
relatives, died immediately, while the truck driver, who came out
unhurt, was detained for investigations.
</P>
<P>
It's reported that 6,808 persons died in about 120,500
accidents occurred in the federal roads last year. 
</P>
