<HEADLINE> Mobile Phone Users Top 500,000 In Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin now has more than
500,000 mobile phone subscribers, giving China's largest port
city an average of 3.4 mobile phones for every 100 residents.
</P>
<P>
The network was launched in late 1989 and it has nearly two
percentage points more subscribers than the national average.
</P>
<P>
Local mobile phone exchanges now have a handling capacity of
nearly 600,000 lines, much higher than the 1,500 lines in the
year 1990.
</P>
<P>
Mobile communication networks are now connected automatically
with counterparts in 304 prefectures and cities across the
country and local mobile communication services are operated by
China Telecom and China Unicom. 
</P>
