<HEADLINE> S.Lankan Local Poll to Get on Web </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 24 (Xinhua) -- For the first time in Sri
Lanka's political history, the election results of the North
Western Provincial Council (NWPC) will go on the Internet after
polling ends on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The election results could be viewed by switching on to http:
//www.laknews.lk from 8 p.m. onwards on January 25.
</P>
<P>
The move, for the benefit of Sri Lankans living abroad, is
sponsored by Lakvision, the pioneer worldwide news service
website.
</P>
<P>
The bitterly contested NWPC election in a single province has
drawn the attention of the whole country, as the outcome will
indicate the relative performance of the main political parties
within the province.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here said it will also hint at the opinion of the
electorate about the performance of the People's Alliance
government at national level over the last four years. 
