<HEADLINE> 5 Serb Hostages Released </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, JANUARY 23 (Xinhua) -- Five Serb civilians abducted
by Kosovo rebels were released on Saturday after the mediation by
the the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe's
(OSCE) ceasefire verification mission.
</P>
<P>
The five Serbs, including two women, were turned over to
members of the OSCE ceasefire verification mission.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile Yugoslav authorities on Saturday also freed nine
Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA) members who had been in custody for
more than a month.
</P>
<P>
Washington welcomed the news, U.S. State Department spokesman
James Rubin said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"We call on both sides to release all detainees and to cease
further detentions," Rubin said.
</P>
<P>
"Such action would serve to build confidence on both sides,
help maintain the ceasefire and facilitate progress in the
negotiations on a political settlement," he said. 
</P>
