<HEADLINE> Venezuelan National Congress Installed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Senator Luis Alfonso Davila, a founder of the ruling "Fifth
Republic Movement (MVR), was elected Senate president and at the
same time president of the Congress of the republic.
</P>
<P>
Lorenzo Azpurua, of the Venezuela Project (PV), and Luis
Lizardi, of the Party for All (PPT), were elected vice president
of the Senate.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Henrique Capriles of the Social Christian Party was e
lected president of the Chamber of Deputies, the lower house of
the two-chamber National Congress.
</P>
<P>
Capriles, a 26-year-old lawyer, is the youngest Chamber of
Deputies president in the Venezuelan history.
</P>
<P>
The National Congress is made up of 207 deputies and 57
senators, including three lifetime senators, who are former
Venezuelan presidents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
