<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1998 GDP Growth Of 9 Percent In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 24 (Xinhua) -- China's Anhui Province had
economic growth of nine percent in 1998 in spite of some serious
natural disasters, official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Anhui's GDP was 283 billion yuan last year, up 9 percent from
1997. Early last year its economic growth fell to below the
national average for the first time since 1992. It was made worse
by excessive snowfalls, floods, and drought.
</P>
<P>
To improve the situation, Anhui restructured the economy and
placed greater importance on the service industry and increased
fiscal support for state-owned sector reforms, grain
distribution, social security, rural and township enterprises,
and the private sector.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that agriculture's added value
production was up 2.3 percent last year and industry's, 9.7
percent. Anhui's revenues were up 12.8 percent to 26.5 billion
yuan in 1998, and farmers incomes per capita edged up 2.8 percent
to 1,860 yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
