<HEADLINE> British Athlete in Drugs Probe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 23 (Xinhua) -- British athletics is set to be
rocked in the next two weeks by the announcement that a senior
athlete has tested positive for drugs.
</P>
<P>
According to the Sunday Telegraph early edition, an athlete
has failed a drugs test and that officials are waiting to
complete the administrative process before making the news public.
</P>
<P>
The athlete is understood to have had the first of two urine
tests show positive traces of banned substances. If the second
test also proves positive, then the athlete will receive an
immediate ban from the sport.
</P>
<P>
UK Athletics, the new governing body of the sport in Britain,
would not reveal the identity of the athlete.
</P>
<P>
"In any situation like this, we have to be officially informed
and, as of now, we haven't had any confirmation of a doping
issue, "said David Moorcroft, the Chief Executive UK Athletics.
"We never comment on doping issues until there is confirmation."
</P>
