<HEADLINE> Decommissioning in N. Ireland May Halt Peace Process: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The Northern Ireland First
Minister David Trimble warned on Saturday the peace process may
have to be "parked" if the Irish Republican Army (IRA) does not
start to hand over its weapons.
</P>
<P>
Trimble's comments came just weeks before the scheduled
handover of power from parliament to a devolved administration in
Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on BBC Radio Ulster's Inside Politics program, he said
there was no question of compromising the basic principles of
peace and democracy.
</P>
<P>
