made, and if it is necessary to park the process for a while so as
to tackle the obstacles created by the paramilitaries, well and
good."
</P>
<P>
"What we don't want is for the process to have a crash-landing
where it is seriously damaged."
</P>
<P>
Trimble said he would "construct a soft landing" if by the time
of handover of power from London there was still no move from the
paramilitaries on weapons.
</P>
<P>
He warned that the paramilitaries would have to clean up their
act and deliver the real peace and evidence of it.
</P>
<P>
Trimble was resisting attempts to set up the new executive for
the Northern Ireland Assembly, which would include two seats for
Sinn Fein, until the IRA hands over some weapons. 
